children.label: type
description: Filter to active queries, inactive queries or all queries

children.label: exact
description: Match query key exactly

children.label: predicate
description: Include queries matching this predicate function

children.label: queryKey
description: Include queries matching this query key

children.label: stale
description: Include or exclude stale queries

children.label: fetchStatus
description: Include queries matching their fetchStatus

children.label: enabled
description:
Set this to `false` to disable automatic refetching when the query mounts or changes query keys.
To refetch the query, use the `refetch` method returned from the `useQuery` instance.
Defaults to `true`.

children.label: staleTime
description:
The time in milliseconds after data is considered stale.
If set to `Infinity`, the data will never be considered stale.

children.label: refetchInterval
description:
If set to a number, the query will continuously refetch at this frequency in milliseconds.
If set to a function, the function will be executed with the latest data and query to compute a frequency
Defaults to `false`.
signature: <TQueryFnData, TError, TQueryData, TQueryKey>) => number | false) | undefined

children.label: refetchIntervalInBackground
description:
If set to `true`, the query will continue to refetch while their tab/window is in the background.
Defaults to `false`.

children.label: refetchOnWindowFocus
description:
If set to `true`, the query will refetch on window focus if the data is stale.
If set to `false`, the query will not refetch on window focus.
If set to `'always'`, the query will always refetch on window focus.
If set to a function, the function will be executed with the latest data and query to compute the value.
Defaults to `true`.

children.label: refetchOnReconnect
description:
If set to `true`, the query will refetch on reconnect if the data is stale.
If set to `false`, the query will not refetch on reconnect.
If set to `'always'`, the query will always refetch on reconnect.
If set to a function, the function will be executed with the latest data and query to compute the value.
Defaults to the value of `networkOnline` (`true`)

children.label: refetchOnMount
description:
If set to `true`, the query will refetch on mount if the data is stale.
If set to `false`, will disable additional instances of a query to trigger background refetches.
If set to `'always'`, the query will always refetch on mount.
If set to a function, the function will be executed with the latest data and query to compute the value
Defaults to `true`.

children.label: retryOnMount
description:
If set to `false`, the query will not be retried on mount if it contains an error.
Defaults to `true`.

children.label: notifyOnChangeProps
description:
If set, the component will only re-render if any of the listed properties change.
When set to `['data', 'error']`, the component will only re-render when the `data` or `error` properties change.
When set to `'all'`, the component will re-render whenever a query is updated.
By default, access to properties will be tracked, and the component will only re-render when one of the tracked properties change.

children.label: onSuccess
description: This callback will fire any time the query successfully fetches new data.

children.label: onError
description: This callback will fire if the query encounters an error and will be passed the error.

children.label: onSettled
description: This callback will fire any time the query is either successfully fetched or errors and be passed either the data or error.
signature: ((data: TData | undefined, error: TError | null) => void) | undefined

children.label: useErrorBoundary
description:
Whether errors should be thrown instead of setting the `error` property.
If set to `true` or `suspense` is `true`, all errors will be thrown to the error boundary.
If set to `false` and `suspense` is `false`, errors are returned as state.
If set to a function, it will be passed the error and the query, and it should return a boolean indicating whether to show the error in an error boundary (`true`) or return the error as state (`false`).
Defaults to `false`.

children.label: select
description: This option can be used to transform or select a part of the data returned by the query function.

children.label: suspense
description:
If set to `true`, the query will suspend when `status === 'loading'`
and throw errors when `status === 'error'`.
Defaults to `false`.

children.label: keepPreviousData
description:
Set this to `true` to keep the previous `data` when fetching based on a new query key.
Defaults to `false`.

children.label: placeholderData
description: If set, this value will be used as the placeholder data for this particular query observer while the query is still in the `loading` data and no initialData has been provided.

children.label: retry
description:
If `false`, failed queries will not retry by default.
If `true`, failed queries will retry infinitely., failureCount: num
If set to an integer number, e.g. 3, failed queries will retry until the failed query count meets that number.
If set to a function `(failureCount, error) => boolean` failed queries will retry until the function returns false.

children.label: isDataEqual
signature: ((oldData: TData | undefined, newData: TData) => boolean) | undefined

children.label: structuralSharing
description:
Set this to `false` to disable structural sharing between query results.
Set this to a function which accepts the old and new data and returns resolved data of the same type to implement custom structural sharing logic.
Defaults to `true`.
signature: boolean | ((oldData: TData | undefined, newData: TData) => TData) | undefined

children.label: getPreviousPageParam
description:
This function can be set to automatically get the previous cursor for infinite queries.
The result will also be used to determine the value of `hasPreviousPage`.

children.label: getNextPageParam
description:
This function can be set to automatically get the next cursor for infinite queries.
The result will also be used to determine the value of `hasNextPage`.

children.label: meta
description:
Additional payload to be stored on each query.
Use this property to pass information that can be used in other places.

children.label: refetchPage
signature: ((lastPage: TPageData, index: number, allPages: TPageData[]) => boolean) | undefined
